 {"id":"orch-go-1018","title":"Probe: How does the OpenAI/GPT plugin work in OpenCode? What models are available via OAuth, what format does it expect, and will orch's openai/gpt-4o model string work end-to-end?","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"investigation","created_at":"2026-02-17T18:26:44.798581-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-02-17T18:27:16.369747-08:00","labels":["area:spawn","triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-1018","author":"dylanconlin","text":"FRAME: Dylan just added default_model config support and GPT aliases to orch (orch-go-1017). He has a GPT Pro account and an OpenCode plugin that enables it. Before he flips the switch with orch config set default_model gpt4o, we need to understand whether orch's model string (openai/gpt-4o) will actually work end-to-end through the plugin — or if there's a format mismatch, missing config, or model availability gap.","created_at":"2026-02-17T18:26:50.733311-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-1018","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating OpenAI plugin in OpenCode fork, tracing model string flow from orch spawn to provider","created_at":"2026-02-17T18:27:29.834865-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-1018","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-02-17-inv-probe-understand-openai-gpt-plugin.md","created_at":"2026-02-17T18:28:03.863861-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-1018","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Writing investigation artifact. Key finding: Codex OAuth plugin filters to GPT-5.x models only - gpt-4o is explicitly removed. Three auth paths identified (OAuth/API key/none), each with different model availability.","created_at":"2026-02-17T18:32:58.008662-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-1018","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Investigation complete. Verdict: openai/gpt-4o will NOT work end-to-end because Codex OAuth plugin whitelists only 6 GPT-5.x models. Three gaps identified: (1) no OpenAI auth in auth.json, (2) gpt-4o removed by Codex plugin, (3) orch aliases misaligned with Codex models. Deliverable: .kb/investigations/2026-02-17-inv-probe-understand-openai-gpt-plugin.md with 7 findings. No discovered work - clean investigation.","created_at":"2026-02-17T18:35:41.418872-08:00"}]}
