+{"id":"orch-go-1022","title":"Fix dashboard blind to tmux agents: reorder scans in serve_agents.go","description":"Three compounding bugs make tmux agents invisible in dashboard:\n\n1. Scan ordering (Critical): serve_agents.go workspace scan (line 598) runs before tmux scan (line 551). Workspace scan claims active tmux agents as 'completed'. Fix: move tmux scan before workspace scan.\n\n2. Beads enrichment skip (Critical): serve_agents.go lines 700-703 skip beads phase comments for workspace-scanned entries, so phase is always null. Fix: include beads enrichment for entries that have a beads_id.\n\n3. active_agent not populated (Important): serve_beads.go GraphNode struct lacks active_agent field. Frontend expects it. Fix: join agent data by beads_id in handleBeadsGraph().\n\n4. WIP store stub (Nice-to-have): wip.ts setRunningAgents() is a no-op, making runningAgentDetailsByIssueId always empty for ALL agents.\n\nRoot cause documented in: .kb/models/agent-lifecycle-state-model/probes/2026-02-17-dashboard-blind-to-tmux-agents.md","repro":"Spawn a Claude CLI tmux agent, check dashboard — shows 'No active agent linked' and status=completed despite agent running in tmux","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-02-17T21:32:46.711102-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-02-17T21:52:27.819159-08:00","labels":["area:dashboard","triage:ready"]}
+{"id":"orch-go-1023","title":"Dashboard work-graph usability improvements: visibility, sorting, and clarity","description":"The work-graph Issues view is structurally working (dependency trees, Ready to Complete, independent issues) but has several usability gaps that make it hard to orient at a glance:\n\n**1. In-progress issues don't visually stand out**\nThe play icon + green subline is too subtle. P1 in-progress bugs should pop — left border accent, background highlight, or similar treatment to the Ready to Complete section.\n\n**2. P1s buried in INDEPENDENT ISSUES**\nTwo P1 bugs are mixed in with 25 P2s. Priority should sort within sections — P1s at top, not mixed by creation order.\n\n**3. 'No active agent linked' is noisy and negative**\nShown on every in-progress issue (partly due to orch-go-1022 tmux bug). Even when fixed, the subline should show agent phase + runtime when linked, and just 'unassigned' or nothing when not — not an alarming message.\n\n**4. Ready to Complete shows stale/already-closed entries**\n980.1 (already closed) and 990 (failed Codex attempt with stale Phase: Complete) still appear. Section should only show issues that are actually open + Phase: Complete.\n\n**5. 27 independent issues is overwhelming**\nMost are backlog. Default should show active work (in-progress + recently created) and collapse/paginate the rest. Or separate 'Active' vs 'Backlog' sections.\n\n**6. Completed agents section competes with Ready to Complete**\nThe completed agents banner (token counts, timing) is useful but visually competes with the more actionable Ready to Complete section. Consider collapsing by default or moving to Completed tab.\n\n**7. Dependency chain header uses issue title as section name**\nChain header shows the title of issue 980.4 which reads oddly as a group name. Should use the root issue title, a computed chain name, or just the root issue ID.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-17T21:45:31.511565-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-02-17T21:47:25.474965-08:00","labels":["area:dashboard","triage:review"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-1023","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Reviewing work-graph dashboard code for usability fixes","created_at":"2026-02-17T21:47:33.469225-08:00"}]}
 {"id":"orch-go-10i","title":"File upstream OpenCode issues: Session TTL, Session Metadata API, Session State endpoint","description":"Phase 3 of lifecycle ownership boundaries decision. Three OpenCode features that would eliminate ~40% of orch lifecycle code (~3,400 lines): 1) Session TTL with configurable expiry - eliminates ghost/phantom/orphan classes, 2) Session metadata API (store beads_id, workspace, tier) - eliminates registry, 3) Session state HTTP endpoint (busy/idle queryable) - simplifies status polling. See .kb/decisions/2026-02-13-lifecycle-ownership-boundaries.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"chore","created_at":"2026-02-13T22:40:24.589221-08:00","created_by":"Test User","updated_at":"2026-02-14T00:03:35.074223-08:00","closed_at":"2026-02-14T00:03:35.074223-08:00"}
